<sect2 id="gimp-layer-lower">
  <title>Lower Layers</title>

  <indexterm>
    <primary>Layer</primary>
    <secondary>Stack managing</secondary>
    <tertiary>Lower layers</tertiary>
  </indexterm>

  <para>
    The <guimenuitem>Lower layers</guimenuitem> command lowers the selected
    layers one position in the layer stack. If the selected layers already end
    at the bottom of the stack, or if there is only one layer, this menu entry
    is disabled.
  </para>

  <sect3>
    <title>Activating the Command</title>
    <para>
      You can access this command
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          From the main menu through
          <menuchoice>
            <guimenu>Layer</guimenu>
            <guisubmenu>Stack</guisubmenu>
            <guimenuitem>Lower Layers</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          By clicking on the down-arrow icon at the bottom of the Layers dialog.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
